app_backend_announcement.announcement: Hey there! Thanks a lot for considering downloading our amazing app. We strongly believe that Jesus is not just a spiritual conqueror but also a winner in the tech domain. If you're excited about our vision and would like to join us as a partner, we'd love to hear from you! Feel free to get in touch with us via any of our social media channels.

Hi there! We're so excited to welcome you to the RAW App - the digital platform of Rise and Walk Ministry. Within the app, you can access many unique features that will enrich your Godly journey and help you connect with like-minded individuals within the ministry. We are here to support you every step of the way, whether you're looking for guidance, encouragement, or an opportunity to connect. Welcome to RAW.

We are incredibly grateful to have you as a part of this ministry. Your presence means a lot to us. You are not just a member; you are a valued partner of this ministry. We want to inform you that starting in August 20th, RAW Grace will be on Tuesdays at 8:45 pm EST. We have decided to move it from Saturdays to open up Saturdays for pursuing Evangelism, as it is the core of our assignment. Our main focus is to win the lost, and we believe that the church is called to maintain the lost. Thank you for your understanding and continued support.

Exciting news 💃🕺🪩! Our 2nd round of The 25:35 Project for the homeless community is underway. On October 19, 2024, RAW Ministry will be hitting the streets of Athens to provide haircuts, clothes, food, prayer, conversation, and love to those in need. Join us to make a difference in the lives of the homeless and show them some love and support.

app_backend_event.eventLocation: This event will be at a place of rest
app_backend_event.eventDescription:
As part of our ministry's commitment to self-care and spiritual rejuvenation, we encourage you to prioritize time with your family and take a break from RAW activities during the R&R week. While we understand that some meetings may be unavoidable, we kindly request that all engagements during this time be approved by the leadership.

Use this opportunity to cherish moments with your loved ones, connect with friends, and dedicate time to self-care. Whether it's enjoying a favorite TV series or engaging in fasting, remember the words from Matthew 11:28, "Come to me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest." True rest and rejuvenation come from seeking God and allowing Him to guide our moments of rest.

Let's remember that self-care is not about indulging in ourselves, but rather connecting with God to find true rest for our body, soul, and spirit. We hope you make the most of this time and look forward to seeing you next week.
Event description test

Get ready for an amazing time! Every week, people from different churches, backgrounds, and career paths come together for Fritay Friday. It's all about celebrating the end of a long week by gathering and connecting as a community of God. There's no agenda, just pure, unfiltered community interaction. Fritay Friday isn't just for Believers – it's for everyone, especially those who don't believe in Jesus. It's our opportunity to sit down together and show that Jesus is about more than just spirituality – He is about community, love and grace. Some battles are not won through prayer, but through community. Don't miss out on free food, free community, and most importantly, a free Jesus!

The main focus of our mission this season is to save souls. Without bringing souls to the Lord, we are not fulfilling our vision. We could engage in 77 different impactful activities for the Kingdom, but if they don't involve bringing souls to the Lord, we have fallen short as a ministry. The park outreach is where we come together as a team and devise innovative ways to save souls. It could be through playing basketball, Uno, walking through the park, playing music, or simply sitting and worshipping in the midst of the darkness. We are confident that if we go, God will be there, because our calling is to save souls. We will consistently bring souls to the Lord. We are appointed and empowered by God to dispel darkness on the streets and to spread the light of Christ in this suffering world. You have been called to do this. You cannot do it alone, but through Christ, everything is possible.

Get ready to make a difference by joining us in fulfilling Jesus's words from Matthew 25:35. Just before Winter arrives, we will be reaching out to the homeless with clothing, blankets, socks, haircuts, and food, and they get it all free of charge to them. Let's show love and compassion by being the hands and feet of Jesus in the upcoming challenging winter of 2025. Your participation and bringing a friend along would mean a lot.

Let's walk in prayer around the city of Athens, just as the Lord told Joshua that wherever he set foot, he would receive it as an inheritance. This is the victory of grace. We will conduct a prayer march throughout the city with the understanding that our approach is focused on spiritually winning the city first, and then making a natural impact.

You are invited to attend the upcoming monthly meeting for the Capturing the Moment team. The purpose of this meeting is to provide a platform for discussing any concerns, sharing updates, and outlining future plans and projects for the team. Please come prepared with any questions, comments, or suggestions related to the previous month's activities or the upcoming month's goals. Your active participation and input are highly valued, and we look forward to productive discussions during the meeting.

We're all set to meet and talk about the Project's progress and outcomes. Let's make sure to jot down any questions ahead of time to keep things running smoothly and make the most of our time together. Please don't hesitate to share your questions, thoughts, or any concerns you might have. Remember, RAW is a ministry that includes all of us, not just one person. Your support and input are highly appreciated!

The purpose of the Prophetic Hour is to lead people towards the Lord through prayer. This event is simple and straightforward. We will gather together, pray, and see what the Holy Spirit desires to do. “Seek me and you will find me.” That’s what the Lord promised unto us.

Event passcode: 100100

You are capable of winning souls unto the Lord. Allow the Holy Spirit and RAW the opportunity to equip you for this assignment.
You are capable of winning souls unto the Lord. Allow the Holy Spirit and RAW the opportunity to equip you for this assignment.

Join us for the leadership prayer call, where we come together to pray as a team and dedicate our time to the Father. Through prayer, we align ourselves with God's plan for our lives, fostering growth, purpose, and vitality in our ministry. Each participant, as a department leader, is encouraged to pray for their team/department, seeking a spirit of workmanship, deep-rooted relationships, strong leadership, and any other intentions guided by the Lord. Let's unite in prayer for the benefit of our entire team.

Gonzalo is tasked with creating a promotion video for the homeless project. This involves defining the video's purpose and target audience, scripting clear and engaging content, and planning the visual flow through storyboarding. He will need to gather the necessary resources, such as equipment, suitable locations, and potential actors or spokespeople. During filming, Gonzalo should focus on achieving high-quality visuals and sound, capturing multiple takes, and obtaining additional footage to enhance the final video. The video should include a strong call to action to encourage viewers to support the project.

CODES
Affirmative = Yes
Copy = Message understood
Disregard = Ignore the previous message
Negative = No
Roger or Roger that = Message understood
What’s your 20? = What’s your location
Do you copy? = Can you hear me
Loud and Clear = Your radio is working
Say Again or Go Again = Say your message again
Over = I’m done with my transmission, ready for your reply
Out = I’m done transmitting for now

10 CODES

10-4 = Transmission is received
10-6 = Stand by, busy
10-7 = Out of service
10-11 = Talking too fast
10-12 = Visitors are present
10-20 = Location
